    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The day following Sunday and preceding Tuesday, traditionally regarded as the second day of the week, but now frequently considered the first day of the week. Named as Moon’s-day on the Roman calendar.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
